1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:05,833
As for the guards, they
wore black and had masks on

2
00:00:07,791 --> 00:00:12,666
With an inscription that read, there
is no god but God. He opens the door

3
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:18,375
He talks to us. The clothing was black,
nothing but black. I only saw black clothing

4
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:23,583
That is it. This is the
clothing the guards wore

5
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:26,875
Interviewer: Was there special
clothing for the prisoners?

6
00:00:27,416 --> 00:00:33,125
No, clothing was given to some
people but not others. I did not see them

7
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:40,125
But it is said that some prisoners were given orange
clothing, while the rest stayed in their own clothes

8
00:00:40,458 --> 00:00:45,708
Of course I was wearing my regular clothes,
but from the sweating my shirt tore

9
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,250
I was wearing a shirt and it was summer
and people were fasting for Ramadan

10
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:55,041
Interviewer: Since that period was
during Ramadan, how was their treatment?

11
00:00:55,708 --> 00:01:04,500
During the day no one spoke to you.
Interrogation started at midnight, after 11 or 12

12
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:11,708
They took people out for interrogation in order. Every
day three or four during Ramadan, three or four at most

13
00:01:12,458 --> 00:01:14,500
Interviewer: Did they bring you a <i>suhoor</i>
[pre-dawn Ramadan meal] and what was it?

14
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:20,041
They brought the pre-dawn meal.
The guard brought it from the daytime

15
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:27,833
Jam, cheese cubes,
mortadella, tomatoes, bread

16
00:01:28,125 --> 00:01:31,000
It was kept with you
inside the solitary cell

17
00:01:32,458 --> 00:01:34,541
Interviewer: Did you write any of
your memories while in the solitary cell?

18
00:01:34,583 --> 00:01:38,166
Yes, I wrote my memories in this
place. Here is where the toilet was

19
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:43,583
And here was a wall, and here was the
toilet wall. Of course my pillow was here

20
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:50,583
There was nothing in the room to write with except a stone we
used to carve into the wall. Of course the wall has been removed

21
00:01:51,041 --> 00:01:56,541
The spot where I carved is no longer
there because the wall has been removed

22
00:01:56,958 --> 00:02:02,666
We carved memories into it with a smooth stone.
We carved the wall to keep ourselves occupied

23
00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:09,500
Interviewer: When they took you for
interrogation, how many people came to get you?

24
00:02:09,708 --> 00:02:15,166
One person. The guard would come
and tell me, turn your face to the wall

25
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:20,708
Then he would put the blindfold on me and handcuff me, then
take me from the solitary cell to the interrogation room

26
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:24,875
Interviewer: How many people
conducted the interrogation?

27
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:31,375
My eyes were blindfolded,
but based on the interrogation

28
00:02:31,791 --> 00:02:35,125
There were two or
three people, two or three

29
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:41,500
Interviewer: Was the interrogation
being recorded on video?

30
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:49,583
Yes, they did record the interrogation. I did
not see it, but I felt they were recording

31
00:02:51,875 --> 00:02:58,208
They were recording me on video of course. It seems there were
people watching elsewhere what was happening during interrogation

32
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:01,625
But my eyes were blindfolded during
interrogation. I could not see anything

33
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,500
Interviewer: What were the
charges brought against you?

34
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:12,750
The charges against me were many, including taking money to
get prisoners out. Of course I never joined any faction at all

35
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:21,916
I was hanging out at a friend's place. It seems my friend had problems
with them, and I was taken to prison without any fault of my own

36
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:25,541
Interviewer: Did your friend get
out or was he still imprisoned?

37
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:33,458
My friend stayed in prison for three months, and it turned
out he was working with them, and I had no knowledge of that

38
00:03:34,875 --> 00:03:41,208
He died while working with them. After that I
cut my ties with him and had no more contact

39
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:48,291
Interviewer: What were the
torture methods they used?

40
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:55,333
What I saw and heard about: suspension on the hoist, and
handcuffing hands behind the back with metal handcuffs

41
00:03:55,833 --> 00:04:00,291
They hang the hoist and lift you up,
then someone jumps and grabs your feet

42
00:04:00,458 --> 00:04:06,458
To increase the weight on you while you are
hanging above the ground, and beating with a whip

43
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:16,041
And suspension on the wall for three to five
hours, hanging on a piece of iron fixed to the wall

44
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:21,375
They hang you on it and lift you off the ground,
and your weight falls mostly on your hands

